    <div class="fr-view">
        <p><strong><span style="font-size: 18px;"><img src="/getmedia/5b15f428-59f5-4f53-91e4-b873e6f6ba61/podcastEpisode15WebEn.jpg" data-strid="991b7b18-9b44-4a38-892c-36a43c15993d" style="width: 400px;" class="fr-fic fr-fil fr-dii" data-name="podcastEpisode15WebEn" data-id="5b15f428-59f5-4f53-91e4-b873e6f6ba61">Episode 15: Innovation as a driver of opportunity</span></strong></p><p>A historically traditional and closed sector, the postal and courier industry has become one of the earliest adopters and the primary testing ground for the latest last-mile innovations over the past decades. Once praised for their silence, postal electric vehicles are now driving the green transition across supply chains globally, advancing a more sustainable future for all. Conversely, technical innovation and increased delivery options and speed can at times encourage irresponsible consumption patterns, offsetting the industry&rsquo;s own environmental achievements. Ahead of the Parcel+Post Expo, the leading global postal trade show, and UPU&rsquo;s annual World Leaders Forum, held on its sidelines, Ian Kerr spoke to Tony Robinson, CEO of UKI Media &amp; Events and Founder of the Expo, about how to combine delivery efficiency with sustainability, which technologies will shape the future of the Post, and why cross-sector collaboration is important to accelerate their adoption.</p>
    </div>



